main event: A witness spotted a single unidentified flying object in Bothell, Washington on January 13, 1961.
interesting points: The object was observed for 6 minutes and was seen traveling straight and level.
The witness provided sketches showing the object's position and altitude relative to the horizon.
The witness had previously reported seeing similar unidentified objects in the Bothell and Everett, Washington areas in 1958, 1959, and 1960.
The witness estimated the speed of the object to be around 2,000 mph and the distance to be about 30 miles away.
An investigation was conducted, but there was insufficient evidence to confirm the existence of any unusual aerial phenomena.
photographs: yes, the report indicates a photograph or film was taken
